        "type": "uofa:Evidence",
        "name": "Synthesis of prior pedicle screw FEA validation studies",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior pedicle screw finite element validation studies spanning 2009–2022, drawing on published literature from Goel, Panjabi, Rohlmann, and FDA CDRH internal analyses. This node consolidates findings on FEA predictive accuracy for Ti-6Al-4V spinal constructs under static compression-bending, providing the methodological and empirical foundation for the acceptance criterion thresholds adopted in this COU. The synthesis informed the choice of E/uval < 1.96 and <10% QoI difference as defensible acceptance bounds, consistent with the broader body of evidence on FEA credibility for Class II spinal devices."
      },
